The paper deals with the problem of recovering a low-rank matrix from phaseless linear projections, which is a common problem in computer vision and signal processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI).
